      <h2 class="section__title"><span class="section__number">01.</span> Project Overview</h1>
      <div class="details">My Role: Product Manager & Designer</div>

      <p>Since its founding in 2011, Buildout has worked to help commercial real estate brokerage offices, brokers, and marketing teams create marketing materials that help them bring in more business, build a stronger brand, and save countless hours of manual work.</p>

      <p>I joined Buildout at an exciting time. They had just <a target="_blank" href="https://www.builtinchicago.org/2017/06/15/buildout-raises-8m-commercial-real-estate-marketing"> raised 8M in funding</a> and had ambitious hopes to build new products that would be <em>an end to end solution for Commercial Real Estate Brokerages</em>.</p>

      <p>I joined as the second UX Designer, and knew that we had our work cut out for us. I ended up wearing the hats of both designer and product manager to ensure that not only was our product solving the needs of our users, but that everyone on the team was aligned with our goals and priorities. I worked with all parts of our team - I rallied our developers behind our product vision, I worked with our support team to ensure they could answer our users’ questions, I managed expectations with business stakeholders, and I spoke directly with our users to really understand how they work.</p>
    </div>

