      <h2 class="section__title"><span class="section__number">02.</span> The pressure was on</h1>

      <p>The vision our small but mighty 3 person product team had been given was very massive:</p>

      <blockquote><em>“An end to end solution for Commercial Real Estate Brokerages”</em>.</blockquote>

      <p>Our first mission was to truly understand what that meant for our current and prospective customers.</p>

      <ol>
        <li>We started by conducting interviews with different commercial real estate offices (current and prospective Buildout users). We spoke with the teams, Managing directors, marketing members, brokers, accountants, and the swiss army of knives of the company. We learned about each person’s role in the office, what their current process looked like, the tools they were using, what was working well, and pain points they had individually and as a team.</li>

        <li>Researched competitors in the space of Contact relationship software, Deal management, and Accounting.</li>

        <li>Researched solutions used by different markets.</li>

        <li>Studied and dissected the various documents, excel spreadsheets, and data that our interviewees sent over.</li>
      </ol>
