      <h2 class="section__title"><span class="section__number">03.</span> Outcomes & Lessons</h1>

      <p>To start, we launched a beta version of our products so we could iterate quickly, test, and validate our work with real data and users. It was exciting to see how much impact our product was making for our customers right from the get-go. People were excited to get in and start adding their data so they could finally have a true view into how their company was doing and how much money they could be expecting at any point. We officially launched to the world in 2020.</p>

      <p>Building Elite was a wild ride with a lot of high and low moments. There were interesting challenges we faced because we were unable to unveil our new products to the world yet. Here are a few lessons we learned:</p>

       <ul>
        <li class="card__list card__list--light-grey">
        Even though new products are very exciting, it is important to remember how your current product enabled you to be successful. At times we put too much effort into the new products, while not continuing to provide value for our current customers.
        </li>
        <li class="card__list card__list--light-grey">Launching a product is more than just making sure the product is going to be a good user experience and technically stable in the external world. There was a lot of internal team infrastructure that we needed in place before we could properly support our new products.</li>
      </ul>

